PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) forensic auditor Trevor White will continue testifying at the state capture commission of inquiry on Tuesday. On Monday, White revealed that controversial businessman Thoshan Panday, or companies linked to him, were paid R47m over 10 months for goods and services provided to the police during the 2010 Fifa World Cup. White compiled a 400-page forensic report that implicated Panday and several high-ranking SAPS officials in KwaZulu-Natal, including then provincial police commissioner Mmamonnye Ngobeni and former crime intelligence memberÂ Col Dhanajaya Naidoo.